📊 Monthly Sales Dashboard – Power BI Project
This Power BI dashboard provides an in-depth analysis of monthly sales performance across multiple years (2013–2016). The project uses dynamic visuals to track and compare sales and costs trends over time.

🔧 Features:
Line Chart: Compares monthly sales and costs across four years with clear trend lines.

Bar Charts: Breaks down the sum of sales and costs by month and year for granular analysis.

Year Selector (Slicer): Allows users to filter the visuals by specific year dynamically.

Custom Visual Styling: Consistent color theme and layout for a clean and user-friendly experience.

Interactive Design: Users can explore insights quickly using bookmarks and slicers.

🧠 Insights Gained:
Identified peak and low-performing months across different years.

Compared sales vs. costs trends to detect profitability periods.

Enabled historical comparison to support better forecasting and decision-making.

🛠️ Tools Used:
Microsoft Power BI

DAX (Data Analysis Expressions)

Power Query
